ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: A wonderful experience that is extremely worthwhile, but not necessarily a completely thorough grounding in the topic.
Yes, for the exposure and the experience of learning with such a passionate leader. But with the caveat that there might be a lot of self-teaching going on too.
A thoroughly enjoyable course, and a shame to lose the professor who runs it!

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: The engagement with the psalms was wonderful, and my final paper taught me a LOT about something that I had had no experience with whatsoever before. So, very useful in that respect! While not closely related at all to my primary research interests, the course definitely gave me a very meaningful experience with an area of the field that I needed to know something about.
This course did give me some references and techniques to use when talking about medieval music. I imagine that it will have little impact on my research.
Exposure to the liturgy, and to its beauty. I'll need to do a little more reading to build my foundation, but the roots of that foundation are there thanks to this course.
